{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "discrete_remesh_stencil",
    "description": "M3 cadence-partition fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §6.1 / §7.3; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.7; bead ess-my4.3.10): the DISCRETE-REMESH worked-trace path — the §6.1 FVM-diffusion stencil with the mesh TOPOLOGY declared `discrete` (a reloaded / AMR-refined mesh) instead of document-literal `parameter`s. It is the direct sibling of mixed_stencil.esm: the SAME RHS D(u[i])/dt = sum_{k in stencil} coeff[i,k] * (u[nbr[i,k]] - u[i]), but `nbr` (neighbour/connectivity table) and `coeff` (per-edge geometry) are now `discrete` variables refreshed on a `remesh` event rather than CONST literals. This realizes the §6.1 worked-trace claim: 'mesh primitives as document literals -> topology partition is CONST (folds at compile); if instead the mesh is reloaded/refined at discrete events, the SAME topology nodes are DISCRETE and move from the artifact into the per-event handler — nothing else changes.' Only the leaf seed changes (nbr/coeff: parameter -> discrete with refresh:{kind:remesh}); the max-propagation does the rest. The gather split is preserved exactly: the inner topology selection index(nbr,i,k) is now DISCRETE while the outer value-load index(u, .) stays CONTINUOUS (class(index(A,e..)) = max(class(A), class(e..)) classes indices independently of the array). So the two topology gathers (nbr, coeff) materialize at the DISCRETE->CONTINUOUS threshold — recomputed by the per-event handler on each remesh event (bind provenance), NOT folded once at compile as in mixed_stencil — exactly the 'discrete-mesh path re-runs only on event' requirement. The hot per-step contraction over u is unchanged and stays CONTINUOUS; topology is never on the hot path, CONST or DISCRETE. Every node carries an `expect_cadence` assertion the partition pass checks against its derived class. Validates against the schema with no evaluator; the golden class summary + materialization set live in tests/conformance/cadence/manifest.json. (The pure-relational discrete edge ENUMERATION — distinct/skolem over a discrete mesh — is the value-invention analogue of this path; its cross-binding materialization-point emission is tracked separately as it currently diverges between bindings.)",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.nux"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "cadence-partition",
      "discrete-remesh",
      "discrete-variable",
      "refresh-trigger",
      "gather-split",
      "materialization-point",
      "stencil",
      "conformance",
      "schema",
      "ess-my4.3.10"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "DiscreteRemeshStencil": {
      "index_sets": {
        "cells": { "kind": "interval", "size": 4 },
        "stencil": { "kind": "interval", "size": 3 }
      },
      "variables": {
        "u": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["cells"],
          "description": "Integrated tracer concentration — CONTINUOUS cadence (changes every step)."
        },
        "nbr": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["cells", "stencil"],
          "description": "Neighbour index table (mesh topology / connectivity), RELOADED from the refined mesh on each AMR remesh event — a discrete variable (shape fixed at setup, values refresh at the remesh event). DISCRETE cadence; materialized into a per-event buffer (bind provenance), recomputed on each remesh — the analogue of mixed_stencil's CONST nbr that folded at compile.",
          "refresh": { "kind": "remesh", "hook": "amr_refine" }
        },
        "coeff": {
          "type": "discrete",
          "shape": ["cells", "stencil"],
          "description": "Per-edge geometric diffusion coefficients derived from the reloaded mesh geometry, recomputed on the AMR remesh event — discrete variable, DISCRETE cadence; materialized into a per-event buffer (bind provenance).",
          "refresh": { "kind": "remesh", "hook": "amr_refine" }
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(u[i])/dt = sum_{k in stencil} coeff[i,k] * (u[nbr[i,k]] - u[i]). The contraction reduces CONTINUOUS terms over a CONST-fixed range -> a CONTINUOUS hot contraction. The inner topology gather nbr[i,k] is DISCRETE (reloaded mesh) and materializes into the per-event handler; coeff[i,k] is DISCRETE and materializes; u-loads are CONTINUOUS. Same gather split as mixed_stencil, only the topology leaf seed is discrete instead of const.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["u", "i"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            },
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 4] }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "expect_cadence": "continuous",
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 4], "k": { "from": "stencil" } },
            "expr": {
              "op": "*",
              "expect_cadence": "continuous",
              "args": [
                {
                  "op": "index",
                  "args": ["coeff", "i", "k"],
                  "expect_cadence": "discrete"
                },
                {
                  "op": "-",
                  "expect_cadence": "continuous",
                  "args": [
                    {
                      "op": "index",
                      "expect_cadence": "continuous",
                      "args": [
                        "u",
                        {
                          "op": "index",
                          "args": ["nbr", "i", "k"],
                          "expect_cadence": "discrete"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "op": "index",
                      "args": ["u", "i"],
                      "expect_cadence": "continuous"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
